eat/8549337/roddy-ricch-the-box-number-one-week-three|url-status=live}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8549975/roddy-ricch-hot-100-number-one-third-week|work=Billboard|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Tops Billboard Hot 100 for Fourth Week, Dua Lipa's 'Don't Start Now' Hits Top 10|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-02-03|access-date=2020-02-03|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8550620/roddy-ricch-the-box-number-one-fifth-week|work=Billboard|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Rules Billboard Hot 100 For Fifth Week, Tones and I's 'Dance Monkey' Swings Into Top Five|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-10|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8551188/roddy-ricch-the-box-number-one-sixth-week|work=Billboard|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Rules Hot 100 For Sixth Week, Dua Lipa Matches Career Best With 'Don't Start Now'|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-02-18|access-date=2020-02-18|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8551757/the-box-tops-hot-100-7th-week|work=Billboard|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Tops Hot 100 For Seventh Week; Dua Lipa Hits Top 5; Justin Bieber, The Weeknd Go Top 10|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-02-24|access-date=2020-02-24|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9326707/roddy-ricch-the-box-number-one-eighth-week|work=Billboard|title=BTS Sets New Career Best on Hot 100 as 'On' Blasts in at No. 4; Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Rules For Eighth Week|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-03-02|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9330849/lady-gaga-stupid-love-hot-100-debut|work=Billboard|title=Lady Gaga's 'Stupid Love' Launches at No. 5 on Hot 100, Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Notches Ninth Week at No. 1|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-03-09|access-date=2020-03-09|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9335717/lil-uzi-vert-3-songs-hot-100|work=Billboard|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Tops Hot 100 For 10th Week, Lil Uzi Vert Launches Three Songs in Top 10|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-03-16|access-date=2020-03-16|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9340653/roddy-ricch-the-box-harry-styles-adore-you-hot-100|work=Billboard|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Leads Hot 100 for 11th Week, Harry Styles' 'Adore You' Hits Top 10|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-03-23|access-date=2020-03-23|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n</ref>\n|-\n|1097\n|April 4, 2020\n|[[The Weeknd]]\n|\"[[Blinding Lights]]\"\n|align=\"center\"|1*\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>\"Blinding Lights\" April 4, 2020:\n* {{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9346375/weeknd-blinding-lights-number-one-hot-100|work=Billboard|title=The Weeknd's 'Blinding Lights' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Doja Cat's 'Say So' Enters Top 10|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=2020-03-30|access-date=2020-03-30|archive-date=|archive-url=|url-status=}}\n</ref>\n|}\n<!--\n;Notes\n-->\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===Artists by total number-one singles===\n<!-- Note to editors:  In the event that two or more artists are tied for a given number of number-one singles, the artist who chronologically reached the count first should be listed above the others; those who reach that count at a later date should not be listed above the other artists with the same count. -->\n\nThe following artists achieved at least one number-one single during the 2020s. A number of artists had number-one singles on their own as well as part of a collaboration. An asterisk (*) denotes that an artist is 